{
  "stem": "21786.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And it became muddy so much so that, I mean, within the half an hour or an hour, depending what they-- what kind of nonsense they wanted to announce, or wanted to do, or just to punish us, we sunk at least, I don't know, up until your ankles, or sometimes even deeper into the mud.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The food which we got depended, again, in what position we would be in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So being a servant to the-- to the head of the block, I got the special ration, probably a double ration, which was usually a kind of a soup which was prepared in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And the soup consisted mostly of water.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And there was something added to it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The favorite addition was ersatz, a replacement of something.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And then there was a-- the meal consisted mostly of turnips.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the turnips, were most of the time, were a little bit rotten, and so that for years, I couldn't even smell turnip.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And occasionally, I mean, we might get a potato, or something, like that, depending simply on the SS man who was in charge, or whoever was in charge, had a better kind of food supply or better mood.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And then we had some kind of a coffee, which was done out coffee ersatz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Altogether, calorie-wise, we got approximately 800 calories, while the rest of Birkenau didn't get more than 500.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people were dying in the camp without any kind of interference.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "The corpses were always taken to the back of the block.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And every morning they were carried forward.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And there came a special commando with hay wagons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And they were thrown on the hay wagons, and 14 men were dragging this hay wagon towards the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
